    s = sum(stack)

        i -= 1
        res += 1

    if s == V:
        res += 1
        stack = []

        res += 1
        break
    stack.append(arr[i])
    i += 1

def main():
    n,v = map(int,input().split())
    u = [int(i) for i in input().split()]
    num = 0
    max_v = 0
    for i in range(n):
        max_v += u[i]
        if max_v == v:
            num += 1
            max_v = 0
        if max_v < v and i == n-1:
            num += 1
            break
        if max_v + u[i+1] > v:
            num += 1
            max_v = 0
            continue
    print(num)

    u = [int(i) for i in input().split()]
    num = 0
    sum_v = 0
    for i in range(n):
        sum_v += u[i]
        if sum_v == v:
            num += 1
            sum_v = 0
            continue

            num += 1
            sum_v = u[i]
            if u[i] == v:
                num += 1
                sum_v = 0
        if i+1 == n and sum_v < v:
            num += 1
    print(num)

            counts = i

            results += 1
            counts = 0
